      "en": "Enter the debugger at the calling stack frame. This is useful to hard-code a breakpoint at a given point in a program, even if the code is not otherwise being debugged (e.g. when an assertion fails). If given, header is printed to the console just before debugging begins. The commands argument, if given, is a list of commands to execute when the debugger starts. Changed in version 3.7: The keyword-only argument header. Changed in version 3.13: set_trace() will enter the debugger immediately, ..."
